      "message": "Should still check this:\n\n  EXPECT_EQ(0, kill(pid_, SIGKILL)) \u003c\u003c ErrorMessage(\"kill\");\n\nHere’s an example of a gross bug that we finally nailed last week that would have been much easier to catch if we had been doing proper checking everywhere: https://crashpad.chromium.org/bug/160.\n\nWe also need to waitpid() for it or we’ll accumulate zombie children:\n\n  int exit_status \u003d 0;\n  EXPECT_EQ(pid_, waitpid(pid_, \u0026exit_status, 0)) \u003c\u003c ErrorMessage(\"waitpid\");\n  EXPECT_TRUE(WIFSIGNALED(exit_status));\n  EXPECT_EQ(SIGKILL, WTERMSIG(exit_status));\n\nHowever it may make more sense to just use the Multiprocess test class that we already have. See test/multiprocess.h. Then all of this bookkeeping is taken care of for you: it’ll wait for the child, you can tell it SetExpectedChildTermination(TerminationReason::kTerminationSignal, SIGKILL), implement the parent/child bits in MultiprocessParent()/MultiprocessChild(), etc.",
